According to the official docs of rxjs: (https://rxjs-dev.firebaseapp.com/guide/observable)

&gt; In an Observable Execution, zero to infinite Next notifications may be delivered. If either an Error or Complete notification is delivered, then nothing else can be delivered afterwards.

You can go for `retry` operator or change your Observable to be of type
`Observable&lt;Data | Error&gt;`, distinguish those emissions and handle respectfully.
```
    setTimeout(() =&gt; {
      observer.next({data: &#39;Some data&#39;});
    }, 7000);

    setTimeout(() =&gt; {
      observer.next({error: &#39;Some error message&#39;});
    }, 8000);
```

